<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?><rss version="2.0"><channel><title>Open Source Hardware</title><link>http://nwazet.com:80/osh</link><description>Open Source Hardware</description><item><title>Adafruit MicroSD Card Adapter For Raspberry Pi</title><link>http://nwazet.com:80/pi-microsd-adapter</link><description>&lt;p&gt;With this microSD card adapter, you can help protect your Raspberry Pi from accidental damage to the SD card port and from file system corruptions caused by knocking the protruding SD card. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The adapter snaps into the Raspberry Pi's SD card slot, but only takes the space of half a card. Insert a micro-SD into it, and get a more compact and safer system.  The micro-SD is easily extracted by pushing on it a second time. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Please be aware that this adapter will not fit into most Raspberry Pi cases.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;Specifications&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Compatible with any micro-SD card&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Protrudes 3mm from the edge of the Raspberry Pi&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5mm thick (clearance from the bottom of the Pi's PCB)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A micro-SD card is &lt;em&gt;not included&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</description><pubDate>Thu, 17 Oct 2013 02:10:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">http://nwazet.com:80/pi-microsd-adapter</guid></item><item><title>Google CODER Jetpack for Raspberry Pi</title><link>http://nwazet.com:80/google-coder</link><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://googlecreativelab.github.io/coder/"&gt;Google Coder&lt;/a&gt; is a Free Open Source package designed to turn a &lt;a href="http://www.raspberrypi.org/faqs"&gt;Raspberry Pi&lt;/a&gt; computer into a simple, tiny, personal web server and web-based development environment. It's just what you need for crafting &lt;a href="http://www.w3schools.com/html/"&gt;HTML&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="http://www.w3schools.com/css/default.asp"&gt;CSS&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href="http://www.w3schools.com/js/default.asp"&gt;Javascript&lt;/a&gt; while you’re learning to code.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;There are a ton of resources for learning &lt;a href="http://www.w3schools.com/html/"&gt;HTML&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="http://www.w3schools.com/css/default.asp"&gt;CSS&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href="http://www.w3schools.com/js/default.asp"&gt;Javascript&lt;/a&gt;: &lt;a href="http://www.codecademy.com/"&gt;Codecademy&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href="https://www.khanacademy.org/cs/programming"&gt;Khan Academy&lt;/a&gt;, to name two—and you can use Coder to accompany this instruction as you experiment with making your own programs. When you're ready to get started, read through the included Hello Coder application to acquaint yourself with how a Coder program works.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For those new to coding for the web, it’s a private platform for building web programs. If you’re already a web programmer, Coder can also be a fun sandbox for experimenting with new ideas, or making demos for other people to learn from.&lt;/p&gt;

